						<p><div class="item">
<h2><a class="listing" style="link" href="/Dossiers/CTA-and-S-T/Selected-publications/Scientific-and-Technological-Cooperation-between-Africa-and-the-European-Union-Past-Achievements-and-Future-Prospects" title="Scientific and Technological Cooperation between Africa and the European Union: Past Achievements and Future Prospects" alt="link">Scientific and Technological Cooperation between Africa and the European Union: Past Achievements and Future Prospects</a></h2>

	
					<p>By European Communities, 2009. Today, entire economies are judged by the investment they make in education, science and technology, culture and innovation. Knowledge, particularly scientifically validated knowledge, is critical for turning the increasingly complex challenges society faces into opportunities for more sustainable development, achieving the Millennium Development Goals and implementing other joint commitments. Scientific relations between what is now the European Union and Africa date back more than 25 years to the launch of the first Science and Technology for Development Programme (STD) in 1983 and have steadily developed since. Under the 6th Research Framework Programme (FP6: 2002-2006), teams from 51 of the 53 African countries filed 3,888 applications for participation in research and other collaborative projects together with their peers from Europe and other continents. 873 of these applications from 39 African countries were successful and received funding of some €93 M.</p>
							<p><span class="date">23/03/2010</span></p>
	<div class="cnt">
	<a class="link" href="/Dossiers/CTA-and-S-T/Selected-publications/Scientific-and-Technological-Cooperation-between-Africa-and-the-European-Union-Past-Achievements-and-Future-Prospects">Read more...</a>
</div>
<br class="cl">
</div>
