						<p><div class="item">
<h2><a class="listing" style="link" href="/Dossiers/CTA-and-S-T/Selected-publications/Gender-perspective-on-COP-15-climate-negotiations" title="Gender perspective on COP-15 climate negotiations" alt="link">Gender perspective on COP-15 climate negotiations</a></h2>

	
					<p>
By WEDO, February 2010. WEDO (Women’s Environment and Development Organization) has produced a short document providing a gender perspective on the outcomes of the December 2009 UNFCCC global climate negotiations in Copenhagen. The document briefly describes the process leading up to COP-15, the meeting itself, the outcome documents and the way forward in 2010.</p>
							<p><span class="date">22/03/2010</span></p>
	<div class="cnt">
	<a class="link" href="/Dossiers/CTA-and-S-T/Selected-publications/Gender-perspective-on-COP-15-climate-negotiations">Read more...</a>
</div>
<br class="cl">
</div>
</p>
						
						<p><div class="item">
<h2><a class="listing" style="link" href="/Dossiers/CTA-and-S-T/Selected-publications/Participatory-learning-and-action-60-Community-based-adaptation-to-climate-change" title="Participatory learning and action 60: Community-based adaptation to climate change" alt="link">Participatory learning and action 60: Community-based adaptation to climate change</a></h2>

	
					<p>
By International Institute for Environment and Development, 2009. It is now become clear that, for poor people, climate change adaptation approaches based on local knowledge and strategies are bound to be more successful than top-down initiatives. The articles in this issue on participatory learning and action focus on the recent approaches to adaptation to climate change utilizing the priorities, knowledge and capacities of local people. Community-based adaptation draws on participatory approaches and methods developed in both disaster risk reduction and community development work and sector-specific approaches.</p>
							<p><span class="date">22/03/2010</span></p>
	<div class="cnt">
	<a class="link" href="/Dossiers/CTA-and-S-T/Selected-publications/Participatory-learning-and-action-60-Community-based-adaptation-to-climate-change">Read more...</a>
</div>
<br class="cl">
</div>
</p>
						
						<p><div class="item">
<h2><a class="listing" style="link" href="/Dossiers/CTA-and-S-T/Selected-publications/Biofuels-and-food-security-Balancing-needs-for-food-feed-and-fuel" title="Biofuels and food security - Balancing needs for food, feed, and fuel " alt="link">Biofuels and food security - Balancing needs for food, feed, and fuel </a></h2>

	
					<p>
By IFPRI, 2008. Biofuel demand is increasing because of a combination of growing energy needs; rising oil costs; the pursuit of clean, renewable sources of energy; and the desire to boost farm incomes in developed countries. In turn, the need for crops—such as maize and sugarcane—to be used as feedstocks for biofuels has increased dramatically. That demand has had a significant and increasing impact on global food systems.</p>
							<p><span class="date">22/03/2010</span></p>
	<div class="cnt">
	<a class="link" href="/Dossiers/CTA-and-S-T/Selected-publications/Biofuels-and-food-security-Balancing-needs-for-food-feed-and-fuel">Read more...</a>
</div>
<br class="cl">
</div>
</p>
						
						<p><div class="item">
<h2><a class="listing" style="link" href="/Dossiers/CTA-and-S-T/Selected-publications/Guidelines-for-rapid-appraisals-of-agrifood-chain-performance-in-developing-countries-Value-chain-analysis-a-standard-guideline" title="Guidelines for rapid appraisals of agrifood chain performance in developing countries - Value chain analysis: a standard guideline?" alt="link">Guidelines for rapid appraisals of agrifood chain performance in developing countries - Value chain analysis: a standard guideline?</a></h2>

	
					<p>








 




  
  

	
	<a href="/var/knowledge/storage/images/media/images/guidelines/295313-1-eng-GB/guidelines.jpg" rel="lightbox[]" >	
	  </a>
	
		
			
	
  	






	 
  





	
By C. da Silva; H. de Souza Filho, Food and Agriculture Organization of the United Nations, 2007.This paper gives guidelines and presents a methodological strategy for the analysis of agrifood value chains. The guideline aims to provide information on the conceptual fundamentals of chain analyses, such as the components of the agrifood chain, research planning and stakeholder validation.</p>
							<p><span class="date">2/03/2010</span></p>
	<div class="cnt">
	<a class="link" href="/Dossiers/CTA-and-S-T/Selected-publications/Guidelines-for-rapid-appraisals-of-agrifood-chain-performance-in-developing-countries-Value-chain-analysis-a-standard-guideline">Read more...</a>
</div>
<br class="cl">
</div>
</p>
											</div> 	
	<br class="cl" />
